You will be using this piece to wrap nearly the entire clip with ribbon before adding your bow. Seal ribbon ends with a little heat (match or lighter). Cut three pieces of ribbon, four inches long. Seal ribbon ends with a little heat (match or lighter). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/71/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/71/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/aid2977413-v4-728px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut the felt and rubber shelf liner the same size-- 1 ¼ by 1/3 of an inch. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/3/3b/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/aid2977413-v4-728px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Be sure the knot is in the middle of the strip and can lay flat. Create a circle shape with each remaining ribbon. Make a loop and add a small dab of glue to the ends. Hold in place until dry and flatten. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/44/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/4/44/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/aid2977413-v4-728px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Pinch the circle right in the center and add a dot of hot glue to the inside center. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b2/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/b2/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/aid2977413-v4-728px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make an “X” with the two circle pieces of ribbon and glue together in the middle of the ribbon “X.”{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d0/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/d0/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/aid2977413-v4-728px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Lay the ribbon with the knot in the middle across the top of the ribbon “X.” Wrap the knot piece ends around the “X” and secure with hot glue. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2b/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/2b/Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet4.jpg/aid2977413-v4-728px-Make-Baby-Hair-Bows-with-No-Slip-Grip-Material-Step-10Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
